data.enText: used when you are emphasizing sth, to mean ‘to the greatest degree possible’
We were in complete agreement.
a complete change
in complete silence
a complete stranger
It came as a complete surprise.

data.chText: 我觉得自己是个十足的笨蛋。
data.enText: I felt a complete idiot.
including all the parts, etc. that are necessary; whole
I've collected the complete set.
a complete guide to events in Oxford
the complete works of Tolstoy

data.chText: 你将按你每一整天的工作领取报酬。
data.enText: You will receive payment for each complete day that you work.

data.chText: 包括，含有（额外部分或特征）
data.enText: including sth as an extra part or feature

data.chText: 这件家具备有组装工具和说明书。
data.enText: The furniture comes complete with tools and instructions for assembly.

data.chText: 此书包括光盘，售价35英镑。
data.enText: The book, complete with CD, costs £35.
finished

data.chText: 办公大楼工程将于年底竣工。
data.enText: Work on the office building will be complete at the end of the year.
the accuracy and completeness of the information

data.chText: 为完整起见，所有名称均用全名。
data.enText: For the sake of completeness, all names are given in full.
to finish making or doing sth

data.chText: 她刚读完法律硕士学位。
data.enText: She's just completed a master's degree in Law.

data.chText: 这项工程必须在一年之内完成。
data.enText: The project should be completed within a year.
to write all the information you are asked for on a form

data.chText: 2 000名顾客填写了我们的调查表。
data.enText: 2 000 shoppers completed our questionnaire.
to make sth whole or perfect

data.chText: 我只差一张卡片就配齐全套了。
data.enText: I only need one more card to complete the set.

simple_means.memory_skill: com 加强 + plet 满的；填满 + e → 特别满 → 完全的

means: 包括，含有(额外部分或特征)

ex.chText: 做完家庭作业后，他就睡觉了。
ex.enText: After finishing his homework, he went to bed.

ex.chText: 你读完那本小说后给我看看。
ex.enText: Let me have the novel when you finish reading it.

ex.chText: 你通常什么时候吃完晚饭？
ex.enText: When do you finish your supper?

synonyms.bx: 最普通用词，指完成某事，常后接名词或动名词，但不可后接动词不定式；也指事件、活动或时期等结束。

ex.chText: 他完成了在欧洲的学业。
ex.enText: He accomplished his education in Europe.

ex.chText: 她因健康状况不佳而未能完成任务。
ex.enText: She failed to accomplish the task because she was in poor health.

synonyms.bx: 较正式用词，尤指通过努力成功地完成某事。

ex.chText: 大会主席向所有与会者表示感谢，就此结束了这次会议。
ex.enText: The chairperson closed the conference by extending his thanks to all the participants.
The party was closed with a sound of applause.

ex.chText: 影片以在伦敦重逢的激动场面结束。
ex.enText: The movie closed with an emotional reunion in London.

synonyms.bx: 尤指（使）某事物以某种方式结束。

ex.enText: Installation of the pipelines was completed last week.

ex.chText: 国民经济计划成功地完成了。
ex.enText: The national economic plan was successfully completed.

ex.chText: 他花了4年时间完成了在欧洲的学业。
ex.enText: It took him four years to complete his education in Europe.

synonyms.bx: 尤指经历较长时间后完成或做成某事物，通常用被动语态。

ex.chText: 这两个国家之间的战争于1898年结束。
ex.enText: The war between these two countries ended in 1898.

ex.chText: 那家工厂的工会同意两天之后结束罢工。
ex.enText: The labour union of the factory agreed to end the strike two days later.

ex.chText: 由于天气不好，聚会早早结束了。
ex.enText: The party ended early due to the bad weather.

synonyms.bx: 指局势、过程、活动等自然结束或被人为终止。

ex.chText: 他的聘约什么时候到期？
ex.enText: When will his contract of employment terminate?
The woman decided to terminate the pregnancy.

synonyms.bx: 指合同、协议等终止或使之终止；也作医学术语，指终止妊娠。

tr: bring to a whole, with all the necessary parts or elements
example: A child would complete the family

tr: come or bring to a finish or an end
example: She completed the requirements for her Master's Degree
The fastest runner finished the race in just over 2 hour

tr: write all the required information onto a form
having every necessary or normal part or component or step
example: a complete set of the Britannica

tr: having come or been brought to a conclusion
example: the affair is over, ended, finished

tr: perfect and complete in every respect

value.def: You use complete to emphasize that something is as great in extent, degree, or amount as it possibly can be.

example.ex: The rebels had taken complete control...
example.tran: 叛乱分子完全控制了局面。

example.ex: It shows a complete lack of understanding by management...
example.tran: 这表明管理层对此完全不了解。

example.ex: The resignation came as a complete surprise...
example.tran: 辞职来得十分意外。

example.ex: He was the complete opposite of Raymond.
example.tran: 他与雷蒙德完全相反。

example.ex: Dozens of flats had been completely destroyed...
example.tran: 许多公寓已经被完全破坏了。

example.ex: Make sure that you defrost it completely.
example.tran: 一定要完全解冻。

example.ex: ...something completely different.
example.tran: 截然不同的事

value.def: You can use complete to emphasize that you are referring to the whole of something and not just part of it.

example.ex: A complete tenement block was burnt to the ground...
example.tran: 整幢公寓大楼被付之一炬。

example.ex: The job sheets eventually filled a complete book.
example.tran: 工作指导卡最终装满了整整一个册子。

value.def: If something is complete, it contains all the parts that it should contain.

example.ex: The list may not be complete.
example.tran: 这个单子可能不全。

example.ex: ...a complete dinner service...
example.tran: 一整套餐具

example.ex: No garden is complete without a bed of rose bushes.
example.tran: 没有玫瑰花圃的花园是不完整的。

example.ex: ...the accuracy and completeness of the information  obtained.
example.tran: 所获信息的精确性和完整性

value.def: To complete a set or group means to provide the last item that is needed to make it a full set or group.

example.ex: Children don't complete their set of 20 baby teeth until they are two to three years old.
example.tran: 小孩要到两三岁才会长齐20颗乳牙。

example.ex: ...the stickers needed to complete the collection.
example.tran: 集全一整套所需的贴纸

value.def: The complete works of a writer are all their books or poems published together in one book or as a set of books.

example.ex: ...the Complete Works of William Shakespeare.
example.tran: 《威廉·莎士比亚全集》

value.def: If one thing comes complete with another, it has that thing as an extra or additional part.

example.ex: The diary comes complete with a gold-coloured ballpoint pen.
example.tran: 这个日记本配有一支金色的圆珠笔。

value.def: If something is complete, it has been finished.

example.ex: The work of restoring the farmhouse is complete...
example.tran: 修复农舍的工作已经完成。

example.ex: It'll be two years before the process is complete.
example.tran: 这个过程需要两年才能完成。

value.def: If you complete something, you finish doing, making, or producing it.

example.ex: Peter Mayle has just completed his first novel.
example.tran: 彼得·梅尔刚刚完成他的第一部小说。

example.ex: ...the rush to get the stadiums completed on time.
example.tran: 为了让各个体育场按时完工进行的匆忙赶工

example.ex: The project is nearing completion...
example.tran: 这个项目即将结束。

example.ex: House completions for the year should be up from 1,841 to 2,200.
example.tran: 今年竣工的房屋将会从1,841幢增加到2,200幢。

value.def: If you complete something, you do all of it.

example.ex: She completed her degree in two years...
example.tran: 她用两年的时间修完了课程，拿到了学位。

example.ex: This book took years to complete.
example.tran: 这本书耗时多年才写完。

value.def: If you complete a form or questionnaire, you write the answers or information asked for in it.

example.ex: Simply complete the coupon below...
example.tran: 填写下面的订货单即可。

example.ex: We ask candidates to complete a psychometric questionnaire...
example.tran: 我们让候选人填写一份心理测试问卷。

example.ex: Use the enclosed envelope to return your completed survey.
example.tran: 请用随信附上的信封将填好的调查表寄回。

value.def: You can use complete to emphasize that someone is skilled at all aspects of a particular activity and is therefore the best example of that kind of person.

example.ex: He was the complete all-round journalist.
example.tran: 他是一名全能的记者。

trans: 完整的想象（或描述、情况）
彻底出乎意料（或给人惊喜）的事（或人）
